query: Who were the Iranian athletes that participated in the 69 Kg category at the 1998 Asian Games? Summarize their performance.
summary: The Iranian athletes who participated in the 69 Kg category at the 1998 Asian Games were Gholam Hossein Pezeshki and Al-Saleh. Pezeshki advanced to Round 2 after a win against Al-Saleh with a score of 5 to 0. However, he then lost to Manukyan in Round 3 with a score of 0 to 10. Pezeshki entered the Repechage round, but he was again unsuccessful as he lost to Jong with a score of 2 to 3. Consequently, Pezeshki did not advance any further in the tournament and ended his participation in the 1998 Asian Games.

query: What trends can be observed in the population change and growth rates among the barangays from 2007 to 2010?
summary: From 2007 to 2010, a big population growth can be seen in the barangays of Bigaa, Cabuyao. Mamatid had the most increase in population, getting first place in rank and has a very good annual growth rate of 3.9%. On the other side, Marinig had the most high annual growth rate of 5.01%, going to second place in rank from its past fourth place. Most barangays have a positive growth rate, but at different levels, giving to the overall 6.34% increase in the total population of the place. But, some barangays like Baclaran and Diezmo have a negative growth rate, showing a small drop in their population from 2007 to 2010.
